  "AC": "Produce a decision-oriented design note that defines the language subset and value model; draws the trust boundary between pure computation and effects; specifies the typed capability/permission protocol, executable constraints, quotas, and audit behavior; includes a threat model and rejected escape-prone features; compares custom interpreter, sandboxed CPython, and WASM/existing-language approaches; and proposes a minimal prototype with tests for permission denial, resource exhaustion, determinism, and sandbox escapes.",
